The paper deals with a common problem in data science, i.e., imbalanced class distribution, and proposes a new sampling method based on kernel density estimation. This method is evaluated on a range of real-life datasets using various classification algorithms, indicating that it could be useful in many different areas of computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
